 that enable the licit life of capitalism-practices that are legally sanctioned, widely replicated, and ordinary, at the same time as they are messy, contested, and, arguably, indefensible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBretonszFrancezParisxHistory. 0aImmigrantszFrancezParisxHistory. 0aMigration, InternalzFrancexHistory. 0aRural-urban migrationzFrancexHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478090243zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478090243/original  a978-3-11-069632-5 Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA